						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the <hi rend="italic">dhvajastaṁbha</hi> in front of the Janārdanasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1712, Sādhāraṇa, Āshāḍha śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1790 A.D., June 26, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It records an appeal against cutting trees in the grove at the sacred spot of Anantapuram in Chintakommadinnepuram as these gave shade and protection to several devotees that assembled there for the festivals.</p>						

						</summary>
